<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-717-684  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 717 684.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  July 30 1990 n379 p12(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>First-time customers need a whole product. (CRN forum: smallbusiness market) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Vertin, Phil.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Resellers of offshore system products must change their marketingapproach in two ways in order to take advantage of the hottestmarket of the 1990s, the computerization of the US' five millionsmall businesses.andP;  The first change involves making systems easierto buy by providing preconfigured systems that include all thecomponents the user will need and eliminate the necessity for theuser to make technical decisions that the user is or feelsunqualified to make.andP;  The second change entails making systemseasier to service and offsetting the higher costs of servicethrough higher margins, achieved by providing higher added valueto the consumer with less cost to the reseller.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Value-Added ResellersMarket EntryMarket PenetrationMarketing StrategyMarket AnalysisCritiqueSmall Business.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>